{"color":"DEFAULT","isTrashed":false,"isPinned":false,"isArchived":false,"textContent":"5a\n1. Ini - this\n2. Itu - that\n3. Kuda - horse\n4. Bagus - good \n5. Kain - cloth\n6. Oleh - by?\n7. Jual - sell\n8. men- - transitive marker\n9. di- - passive marker\n10. an- - locative trigger (parang sa Tagalog)\n11. pen- - doer of action (-er in English)\n5b\nInflectional: men- (transitive marker)\nDerivational: -an (locative trigger) pen- (doer)\n5c\n1. False\n2. True\n3. True\n5d. Performing a possessive phrase is formed by: possessee possessor, with the example \"Kuda Ali\", Ali is the possessor and the horse is the possessee.\n5e. \"Kuda bagus ini\" this good horse, \"kuda Ali\" Ali's horse. There is no copula so we infer that it is an A=B phrase making us have \"This good horse is Ali's horse\" or \"This good horse is Ali's\"\n5f\n1. Jualan Ali kain.\n2. Ini kuda bagus.\n3. Kuda ini bagus.\n5g\n1. pendidik - \"pen-\" means doer so this means educator or \"teacher\n2. didikan - \"-an\" is a locative trigger so this means place of education or \"school\"","title":"Lingg Pset 2","userEditedTimestampUsec":1663669437327000,"createdTimestampUsec":1663660433192000,"textContentHtml":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">5a<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">1. Ini - this<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google 